= BIT: test BITs

|=Addressing Mode |=Opcode Syntax |=In Hex |=Length |=Cycles |
|Zero Page        |`BIT $44`      |$24     | 2      | 3      |
|Absolute         |`BIT $4400`    |$2C     | 3      | 4      |

**Flags affected:** S V Z

BIT sets the [[Zero]] Flag as if the argument was [[AND]]ed with the Accumulator.
It also sets the [[Sign]] flag to the value of Bit 7 and the [[Overflow]] flag
to the value of Bit 6 of the value of the argument.

